{
  "stem": "15768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because our sponsor had to not only obligate himself to make sure that we would be absolutely no burden to anyone-- the government, that is, or the taxpayers in the United States.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we needed a clean bill of health, which unfortunately, my father really didn't have.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But somehow or other, we squeaked him through.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as we left the consulate after a full day of questionnaires, and examinations, and paperwork, we had tickets to sail out of Antwerp on May 15th, 1940, and of course, joyfully went back to Brussels and made preparations for this all-important journey that we were going to finally be able to take.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As things happen, on May 10th, the lowlands were invaded.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We woke up to thunder in the sky.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And while standing on the balcony of our apartment house and looking at the sky, unbelieving what, what was to be seen, the back of the house received a bomb and was bombed off.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember standing on the balcony and watching the destruction and ultimately, the carts that were taking away dead people, injured people, and realizing that this was a, a disaster all around for everyone.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think it was a lot too chaotic really for any explanation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father went dashing off to the other part of town to confer with other refugee families that we had gotten to know and trying to think of some route of escape out of this.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because he felt if, if he were anywhere where the Germans would find him, he would be sent back to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so he was very desperate to move ahead.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The last news that we had had, my Uncle Moritz was with his family in Paris, with his wife's family.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
